👉 “How will you implement dependent dropdowns (State → City) using Angular and API?”
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ Perfect Interview Answer (Structured)
👉 Start like this:
“First, I will create two APIs — one to fetch states and another to fetch cities based on stateId.”
👉 Then explain flow:
*“On component load (ngOnInit), I will call the state API and bind the data to the state dropdown using ngFor.”
👉 Then explain dependency:
“When the user selects a state, I will capture the stateId using the change event or reactive form valueChanges.”
👉 Then API call:
“Based on the selected stateId, I will call the city API and populate the city dropdown dynamically.”
👉 Then add best practice:
“I will also reset the city dropdown when the state changes to avoid showing old data.”

1. What is @ViewChild?
Used to access a child component / DOM element inside a parent component.
Example: accessing an input box or child component methods.
👉 Simple: Parent component se child ko control karna
@ViewChild('inputRef') input: ElementRef;
2. State → City dropdown (dependent dropdown)
👉 Flow:
Call API to get states
When state selected → call city API
Update city dropdown
onStateChange(stateId) {
  this.api.getCities(stateId).subscribe(res => {
    this.cities = res;
  });
}
👉 HTML:
<select (change)="onStateChange($event.target.value)">
<select>
<select>
  <option *ngFor="let city of cities">{{city.name}}</option>
</select>
