5. What is constant file?
File where we store fixed values
Example: API URLs, messages
export const API_URL = 'http://example.com';
6. constructor vs ngOnInit()
constructor	ngOnInit
Runs first	Runs after constructor
Used for DI (dependency injection)	Used for logic/API calls
No lifecycle	Lifecycle hook
👉 Simple: constructor = setup, ngOnInit = logic
7. Subject vs BehaviorSubject vs ReplaySubject
Type	Behavior
Subject	No previous value
BehaviorSubject	Holds latest value
ReplaySubject	Stores multiple old values
👉 Example:
BehaviorSubject → always gives last value to new subscriber
8. What is async pipe?
Automatically subscribes & unsubscribes observable
{{ data$ | async }}
👉 No need to manually subscribe
9. 5 RxJS operators (simple)
map() → modify data
filter() → filter values
switchMap() → cancel previous API call
mergeMap() → run multiple API calls
debounceTime() → delay execution
10. Common error handling
👉 Using interceptor (best practice)
catchError(error => {
  console.log(error);
  return throwError(error);
})
👉 Or global HTTP interceptor
