Q1) NPM & node_modules
Node Package Manager (NPM) → Used to install and manage project libraries.
node_modules → Folder where all installed packages are stored.

👉 Short answer:
NPM manages dependencies, and node_modules contains all installed libraries.

Q4) Annotations / Metadata
Metadata = information about a class
In Angular, it is written using decorators like @Component

👉 Short answer:
Annotations (metadata) tell Angular how a class should behave using decorators like @Component.
